Retrieval-Augmented Generation
It uses a knowledge graph to efficiently store and retrieve information.

knowledge graph
It stores and retrieves information using a graph structure.

LightRAG
The system uses LightRAG for retrieval and generation tasks.<SEP>LightRAG is a Retrieval-Augmented Generation system.<SEP>A framework used for knowledge graph processing.

OpenAI
OpenAI is a major artificial intelligence organization that provides the service for LightRAGâ€™s backend.

Ollama
Ollama is another AI organization that contributes to the backend of LightRAG, enabling efficient information retrieval and generation tasks.<SEP>Ollama serves local language and embedding models.

Hugging Face
Hugging Face is a backend for LightRAG.

PostgreSQL
A database system that can be used as LightRAG's production setting for storage of data.

LLM
Large Language Model, a type of AI.

Knowledge Graph
A structure for organizing information in a systematic way.

tokens
A measure of the amount of information a system can work with.

gemma2
A method (gemma2) is a reasonable choice for generation and nomic-embed-text for embeddings in lightweight CPU or low-memory GPU environments.

nomic-embed-text
Nomic-embed-text is used for embeddings, an aspect of local language models.

context size
Context size is a parameter that can be adjusted to optimize performance and memory usage.

overlap
Overlap is a parameter influencing model processing and memory utilization, often related to chunk size and its impact.

chunk size
Chunk size, a parameter in the model's processing, adjusts memory usage for optimal performance.
